com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface ElementSetDef


  • public interface ElementSetDef
    Represents a single element set definition, and may define content for multiple entries in an ElementList.
    See Also:
    LocalElementSetDefDb, ElementSetDefEntry

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears members from an ElementSetDef. Useful for object reuse.

      • setId

        int setId()
        The identifier value associated with this element set definition. Any element list content that leverages this definition should have the ElementList.setId(int) matching this identifier. 0 - 15 are the only values valid for local set definition content. Values can be higher for global set definition content.
        Returns:
        the setId

      • setId

        void setId(int setId)
        The identifier value associated with this element set definition. Any element list content that leverages this definition should have the ElementList.setId(int) matching this identifier. 0 - 15 are the only values valid for local set definition content. Values can be higher for global set definition content. Must be in the range of 0 - 32767.
        Parameters:
        setId - the setId to set

      • count

        int count()
        The number of ElementSetDefEntry structures contained in this definition. Each entry defines how to encode or decode an ElementEntry.
        Returns:
        the count

      • count

        void count(int count)
        The number of ElementSetDefEntry structures contained in this definition. Each entry defines how to encode or decode an ElementEntry. Must be in the range of 0 - 255.
        Parameters:
        count - the count to set

      • entries

        ElementSetDefEntry[] entries()
        The array of entries this definition will use. Each entry defines how to encode or decode an ElementEntry.
        Returns:
        the entries array
